cancelRunningPayments(address).details: It's up to the the implementation to keep up with what has been         paid out or not.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance to process its to payments.

claimAll(address).details: This function should be callable if the `_msgSender` is an `activePaymentReceiver`.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance address that processes all claims from `_msgSender`.

claimForSpecificStream(address,uint256).details: If for a specific streamId, the tokens could not be transferred for some reason, it will added         to the unclaimableAmounts of the `paymentReceiver`, and the amount would no longer hold         any co-relation with he specific streamId of the `paymentReceiver`.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance address that processes the `streamId` claim               from `_msgSender`.
params.streamId: The ID of the streaming payment order for which claim is being made.

claimPreviouslyUnclaimable(address,addre.details: This function should be callable if the _msgSender has unclaimedAmounts.

params.client: The IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2 instance address that processes all claims from _msgSender.
params.receiver: The address that will receive the previously unclaimable amount.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which cliff is fetched.

returns._0: cliff duration of the payment order.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which end is fetched.

returns._0: end timestamp of the payment order.

params.target: The target address to grant the role to.

params.targets: The target addresses to grant the role to.

identifier().details: The identifier is defined as the keccak256 hash of the module's         abi packed encoded major version, url and title.

init(address,(uint256,uint256,uint256,st.details: CAN be overridden by downstream contract.MUST call `__Module_init()`.

params.configData: Variable config data for specific module                   implementations.

isActivePaymentReceiver(address,address).details: This function is for convenience and can be easily figured out by other means in the codebase.

returns._0: true if the paymentReceiver is active for the payment client.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: We imitate here the EIP2771 Standard to enable metatransactions         As it currently stands we dont want to feed the forwarder address to each module individually and we decided to         move this to the orchestrator.

params.forwarder: The contract address to be verified.

returns._0: bool Is the given address the trusted forwarder.

processPayments(address).details: It's up to the the implementation to keep up with what has been         paid out or not.Currently callback functions on token transfers are not supported and thus not checked.         This could lead to a failed transaction which could influence the batched processing of         payments.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance to process its to payments.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which the releasable amount is fetched.

returns._0: releasable amount of the stream with id = streamId.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which released is fetched.

returns._0: released amount of the payment order.

removeAllPaymentReceiverPayments(address.details: this function calls `_removePayment` which goes through all the payment orders for a `paymentReceiver`.         For the payment orders that are completely streamed, their details are deleted in the         `_claimForSpecificStrea` function and for others it is deleted in the `_removePayment` function only,         leaving the currently streaming tokens as balance of the paymentClient itself.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance address from which we will remove the payments.

removePaymentForSpecificStream(address,a.details: the detail of the wallet that is being removed is either deleted in the `_claimForSpecificStream`         or later down in this function itself depending on the timestamp of when this function was called.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance address from which we will remove the payment.
params.paymentReceiver: Address of the paymentReceiver whose payment order is to be removed.
params.streamId: The ID of the paymentReceiver's payment order which is to be removed.

params.target: The target address to revoke the role from.

params.targets: The target addresses to revoke the role from.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which start is fetched.

returns._0: start timestamp of the payment order.

params.streamId: Id of the wallet for which the streamed amount is fetched.
params.timestamp: the time upto which we want the streamed amount.

returns._0: streamed amount of the stream with id = streamId.

trustedForwarder().details: We imitate here the EIP2771 Standard to enable metatransactions.         As it currently stands we dont want to feed the forwarder address to each module individually and we decided to         move this to the orchestrator.

returns.amount: Amount of tokens that could not be claimed.

params.order: The IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2 Order that needs to be checked.

returns._0: valid Bool if the Payment Order is valid.

viewAllPaymentOrders(address,address).details: the paymentReceiver must be an active paymentReceiver for the particular payment client.

returns._0: all streams for a particular payment client and payment receiver.

cancelRunningPayments(address).notice: Cancels all unfinished payments from an {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance.

claimAll(address).notice: claim everything that the paymentClient owes to the `_msgSender` till the current timestamp.

claimForSpecificStream(address,uint256).notice: claim the total amount up til block.timestamp from the client for a payment order with id = streamId         by _msgSender.

claimPreviouslyUnclaimable(address,addre.notice: claim every unclaimable amount that the paymentClient owes to the _msgSender and send it to a         specified receiver.

cliffForSpecificStream(address,address,u.notice: Getter for the cliff duration of a particular payment order with id = streamId associated         with a particular paymentReceiver.

endForSpecificStream(address,address,uin.notice: Getter for the stream end timestamp of a particular payment order with id = streamId associated         with a particular paymentReceiver.

grantModuleRole(bytes32,address).notice: Grants a module role to a target address.

grantModuleRoleBatched(bytes32,address[].notice: Grants a module role to multiple target addresses.

isActivePaymentReceiver(address,address).notice: Tells whether a `paymentReceiver` has any pending payments for a particular client.

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: Checks if the provided address is the trusted forwarder.

processPayments(address).notice: Processes all payments from an {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2} instance. Please note:         this function does not support callbacks on transfer of tokens.

releasableForSpecificStream(address,addr.notice: Getter for the amount of releasable tokens for a particular payment order with id = streamId associated         with a particular paymentReceiver.

releasedForSpecificStream(address,addres.notice: Getter for the amount of tokens already released for a particular payment order         with id = streamId associated with a particular paymentReceiver.

removeAllPaymentReceiverPayments(address.notice: Deletes all payments related to a paymentReceiver & leaves currently streaming tokens in the         {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2}.

removePaymentForSpecificStream(address,a.notice: Deletes a specific payment with id = streamId for a paymentReceiver & leaves currently streaming         tokens in the {IERC20PaymentClientBase_v2}.

revokeModuleRole(bytes32,address).notice: Revokes a module role from a target address.

revokeModuleRoleBatched(bytes32,address[.notice: Revokes a module role from multiple target addresses.

startForSpecificStream(address,address,u.notice: Getter for the start timestamp of a particular payment order with id = streamId associated         with a particular paymentReceiver.

streamedAmountForSpecificStream(address,.notice: Calculates the amount of tokens that has already streamed for a particular payment order         with id = streamId associated with a particular paymentReceiver.

unclaimable(address,address,address).notice: Getter for the amount of tokens that could not be claimed.

validPaymentOrder((address,address,uint2.notice: Function that checks if the given PaymentOrder was valid.

viewAllPaymentOrders(address,address).notice: See all active payment orders for a paymentClient associated with a particular paymentReceiver.
